The administration block of Rongo University in Migori County. [Courtesy of Rongo University]  A 23-year-old student of Rongo University in Migori County is suspected to have died by suicide.  Police have since identified the deceased as Collins Kipkirui, a Third Year who was pursuing a Bachelor’s Degree in Education (Mathematics and Chemistry).  Police said students, who were heading to class, saw Kipkirui’s body hanging from a rope tied to a tree near the hostels.  South Kamagambo chief, Joseph Nyamanga, said no suicide note was found on the deceased. Rongo University Vice-Chancellor Samuel Gudu said they were yet to establish the reason behind Kipkirui’s suspected suicide.  The student’s body was taken to Rosewood mortuary in Rongo Town.  By Erick Abuga | 1 hour ago By Harold Odhiambo | 11 hours ago By Robert Amalemba | 17 hours ago By James Omoro | 17 hours ago